-- UK police search offices of Daily Star newspaper
-- 
-- Fri Jul 8, 2011 4:48pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/08/us-newscorp-hacking-star-idUSTRE7673H020110708

 

 LONDON, Jul  (Reuters) - Police investigating allegations of phone hacking by newspaper journalists were on Friday searching the offices of the Daily Star tabloid, a police source said. 

 Investigations into hacking have so far centered on the News of the World newspaper. The Star is owned by businessman Richard Desmond and is not connected to News Corp, the owner of News of the World. (Reporting by  Keith Weir )